Hi <%= @user.display_name %>!!

We are so grateful that you want to be a volunteer at SOF! Volunteering at SOF is a great way to meet a lot of different people and get a chance to help realize Sweden’s biggest student festival! It will be a couple of intense but amazing days, so it is important that you have read the contract thoroughly.

When you’ve chosen and agreed to one or more shifts, your application is binding. This means that we expect that you show up for your shift at least 15 minutes before it starts in order to check in. If you log onto your profile on sof17.se you will be able to see the shifts that you have applied to.

Before the festival there will be a <b>mandatory info-meeting the 1st of May at 6:00 PM in C1 at Campus Valla.</b> As a volunteer at Sweden’s most amazing student happening you work ideally, which means that you won’t get any monetary compensation for any of the work that you perform or the possible trips that might come with, to and from the festival.
Other than the discount on the tickets that you can use in the web shop, you will get an <b>amazing kravall on the 4:th of May as a thanks that you volunteer.</b>
During the shifts that you work, you will also get a meal. As a volunteer at SOF, you represent the festival and therefore we expect the following of you:

<ul>
  <li>You’re committed and perform the tasks that you are assigned, as well as being present during the time which you are scheduled.</li>
  <li>You show up well-rested and sober in time for your shifts.</li>
  <li>If you become sick and are unable work your assigned shift a medical certificate is required in order for your absence to be accepted.</li>
</ul>

If you have any questions, don’t hesitate to send and e-mail to personal@sof17.se!
